				<p class="card-text">
					Bird migration is a remarkable phenomenon where millions of birds
					travel thousands of miles between breeding and wintering grounds.
					These journeys are perilous, with many species relying on conserved
					stopover habitats. <span class="read-more-content">
						Understanding and protecting these migratory routes is vital for
						the survival of many bird species, ensuring that they can continue
						their incredible journeys.</span>
				</p>
